Name: Ba-122
Sentence: No significant difference in the magnetization vs temperature curves measured by a SQUID magnetometer was observed between the Ag and Ag-Sn sheathed tapes, all samples showing the onset of transition at around 37 K. SEM-EDX analysis for Ba-122 core showed no observable signal of the Sn above the back ground level even near the interface within the resolution of the SEM.

Among various families of iron-pnictides superconductors, 122 type of AEFe 2 As 2 (AE=alkaline earth) [2] is mostly of practical interest, because of its high transition temperature, T c , (~39 K), very high upper critical field, H c2 , (>50 T) and relatively small anisotropy (Î³<2) .
